name: PartyRoleIdentifier
label: party role identifier
definition: sequence of characters, capable of uniquely identifying a party based on a specific role that they play in some context

name: PartyRoleIdentificationScheme
definition: system for allocating identifiers to roles that parties play
label: party role identification scheme

name: TaxIdentifier
label: tax identifier
explanatoryNote: Tax identifiers are used for various tax-related purposes in the United States and in other countries under the Common Reporting Standard (CRS).
definition: identifier assigned to a taxpayer that enables compulsory financial charges and other levies to be imposed on the taxpayer by a governmental organization in order to fund government spending and various public expenditures

name: TaxIdentificationScheme
definition: identification scheme used to identify taxpayers in some jurisdiction
label: tax identification scheme

name: hasMailingAddress
definition: identifies a physical address where an independent party can receive communications, including letters and packages
label: has mailing address
